<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<accessibility-service xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:description="@string/accessibility_service_description"
    android:accessibilityEventTypes="typeAllMask"
    android:accessibilityFlags="flagDefault|flagRequestFilterKeyEvents"
    android:accessibilityFeedbackType="feedbackGeneric"
    android:canRequestFilterKeyEvents="true"
    android:canRetrieveWindowContent="false"
    android:notificationTimeout="100"
    android:settingsActivity="org.localforge.alicia.SettingsActivity" />

<!--
Accessibility Service Configuration for Alicia Hotkey Detection

This configuration enables the HotkeyAccessibilityService to:
- Intercept hardware button key events (volume, power)
- Detect triple-tap volume up
- Detect long-press power button
- Provide haptic feedback

Permission Requirements:
- BIND_ACCESSIBILITY_SERVICE in AndroidManifest.xml
- User must manually enable in Settings > Accessibility

Key Configuration Parameters:
- accessibilityEventTypes: typeAllMask - Listen to all events
- accessibilityFlags:
  * flagDefault - Standard behavior
  * flagRequestFilterKeyEvents - Request to filter key events
- canRequestFilterKeyEvents: true - Essential for hardware button detection
- canRetrieveWindowContent: false - We don't need window content
- notificationTimeout: 100ms - Minimal timeout for responsiveness

Note: This service does NOT read screen content or user data.
It only listens for hardware button combinations.
-->
